<chapter id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para>
&aki; is an <acronym>IRC</acronym> client for &kde;. The difference between
&aki; and other <acronym>IRC</acronym> clients is that &aki; has an extensive
plugin interface.
</para>
</chapter>

<chapter id="using-kapp">
<title>Using &aki;</title>

<para>
To start &aki;, open it by going to
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Kickoff</guimenu>
<guisubmenu>Applications</guisubmenu>
<guisubmenu>Internet</guisubmenu>
<guimenuitem>IRC Client (Aki)</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
.
</para>

<procedure><title>First time starting &aki;</title>
<step>
<para>
After starting &aki;, you will be presented with a <guilabel>Welcome to
Aki</guilabel> dialog. <mousebutton>Press</mousebutton>
<guibutton>Next</guibutton> to continue.
</para>
</step>
<step>
<para>
To create an identity, enter your <guilabel>Real name</guilabel> as well as any
nicknames you will use on <acronym>IRC</acronym>.
<mousebutton>Press</mousebutton> <guibutton>Next</guibutton> when you have
completed entering this information.
</para>
</step>
<step>
<para>
Setup the server you would like to connect to. Enter information concerning
<guilabel>Servers</guilabel>, <guilabel>Channels</guilabel>, and if you have an
account on the <acronym>IRC</acronym> server, the information required to
identify with. <mousebutton>Press</mousebutton> <guibutton>Finish</guibutton> when
you have completed entering this information.
</para>
</step>
</procedure>

